    "explanation": "<p>There are total 5 isomers (including stereoisomers) of compound having formula $ \\mathrm{C}_{4} \\mathrm{H}_{9} \\mathrm{Br} $</p>\n<p>1-bromobutane $ \\rightarrow $</p>\n<p>$ \\mathrm{CH}_{3}-\\mathrm{CH}_{2}-\\mathrm{CH}_{2}-\\mathrm{CH}_{2}-\\mathrm{Br} $</p>\n<p>2-bromobutane $ \\rightarrow $</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m62i0f3b/ef9188d9-2182-4c83-8a54-4639367ffe67/b5275770-d5c6-11ef-8ba5-7d7611532882/file-jaoe38c1m62i0f3c.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m62i0f3b/ef9188d9-2182-4c83-8a54-4639367ffe67/b5275770-d5c6-11ef-8ba5-7d7611532882/file-jaoe38c1m62i0f3c.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"TG EAPCET 2024 (Online) 10th May Evening Shift Chemistry - Isomerism Question 2 English Explanation 1\"></p>\n<p>( $ d $ and $ l $ form)</p>\n<p>1-bromo-2-methyl propane $ \\rightarrow $</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m62i0ygg/2a31ba5f-6953-4363-86db-9beadeb393c6/c41cd700-d5c6-11ef-8ba5-7d7611532882/file-jaoe38c1m62i0ygh.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m62i0ygg/2a31ba5f-6953-4363-86db-9beadeb393c6/c41cd700-d5c6-11ef-8ba5-7d7611532882/file-jaoe38c1m62i0ygh.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"TG EAPCET 2024 (Online) 10th May Evening Shift Chemistry - Isomerism Question 2 English Explanation 2\"></p>\n<p>2-bromo-2-methyl propane $ \\rightarrow $</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m62i1pem/c691fbe9-6de5-4514-8e13-648abc33c2d5/d8ee1fe0-d5c6-11ef-8ba5-7d7611532882/file-jaoe38c1m62i1pen.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m62i1pem/c691fbe9-6de5-4514-8e13-648abc33c2d5/d8ee1fe0-d5